<TITLE> BSEHR to help ailing sisters again </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 9 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Society for the Enforcement of Human Rights (BSEHR) will again take initiatives to treat sisters Rita and Mita apparently suffering from a relapse of mental illness. Both the sisters have fallen ill and are keeping themselves indoors recently, said their neighbours to the bdnews24.com correspondent, who went to the their Mirpur-6 home Saturday afternoon, but could not meet them. The head of the pathology department of Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University (BSMMU), Prof Mohammad Kamal, said the sisters might need medical attention again. Elina Khan, executive director of BSEHR, said they would again take initiatives to get them treated. "We kept them under observation for six months. On hearing the news of their recent relapse to mental instability, we have sent people to investigate. We will take necessary steps if necessary," she said. Following the death of their mother, the two sisters, Rita a doctor and Mita an engineer, went into self-confinement before being rehabilitated in 2005. bdnews24.
